      <div class="q-explanation"><strong>Correct Answer: D.</strong> Total sum of 6 values \(= 6 \times 14 = 84\). Remove the value 8: new sum \(= 84 - 8 = 76\). New mean \(= \dfrac{76}{5} = 15.2\). A common error is computing \(\dfrac{84}{5}\) without subtracting — always adjust both the sum AND the count when removing a value.</div>
