      <ul class="q-options">
        <li><button onclick="checkAnswer(this,'A','math')">A) \(x = -4\) only</button></li>
        <li><button onclick="checkAnswer(this,'B','math')">B) \(x = 1\) only</button></li>
        <li><button onclick="checkAnswer(this,'C','math')">C) \(x = -4\) and \(x = 1\)</button></li>
        <li><button onclick="checkAnswer(this,'D','math')">D) No real solution</button></li>
      </ul>
      <div class="q-explanation"><strong>Correct Answer: B.</strong> Square both sides: \(3x + 13 = (x+3)^2 = x^2 + 6x + 9\). Rearrange: \(x^2 + 3x - 4 = 0 \Rightarrow (x+4)(x-1) = 0\), giving \(x = -4\) or \(x = 1\). Check \(x = -4\): left side \(= \sqrt{3(-4)+13} = \sqrt{1} = 1\); right side \(= -4+3 = -1\). Since \(1 \neq -1\), \(x = -4\) is an extraneous solution. Check \(x = 1\): \(\sqrt{3(1)+13} = \sqrt{16} = 4\); \(1+3 = 4\) ✓. Always check for extraneous solutions when squaring both sides.</div>
    </div>

